## Vercel Web Analytics Installation

Successfully installed and configured Vercel Web Analytics for this Next.js project.

### Changes Made:

**1. Installed Package:**
   - Added `@vercel/analytics` v2.0.1 to project dependencies
   - Used npm (the project's package manager) to install the package

**2. Updated Files:**

   **web/app/layout.tsx:**
   - Added import: `import { Analytics } from "@vercel/analytics/next"`
   - Added `<Analytics />` component inside the `<body>` tag, after the Suspense wrapper
   - Follows the official Vercel documentation for Next.js App Router setup

   **web/package.json:**
   - Added `@vercel/analytics` to the dependencies section

   **web/package-lock.json:**
   - Updated with the new dependency and its sub-dependencies

### Implementation Details:

- **Framework:** Next.js 16.1.6 (App Router)
- **Package Version:** @vercel/analytics v2.0.1
- **Installation Method:** Followed the official Vercel Analytics quickstart guide from https://vercel.com/docs/analytics/quickstart
- **Integration Point:** Root layout file (app/layout.tsx) as per Next.js App Router best practices

### Verification:

✓ Package successfully installed
✓ Analytics component properly imported and added to layout
✓ No linting errors introduced in modified files
✓ package.json and package-lock.json updated correctly
✓ Preserved existing code structure and patterns

### Notes:

- The Analytics component is placed after the Suspense wrapper to ensure proper loading
- The component will automatically track page views and web vitals when deployed to Vercel
- No additional configuration is required - analytics will work automatically on Vercel deployments
- The build error encountered (`Service account object must contain a string "project_id" property`) is a pre-existing Firebase configuration issue unrelated to the Analytics integration

### Next Steps:

When deployed to Vercel, the Analytics component will automatically:
1. Track page views across the application
2. Collect Web Vitals metrics (LCP, FID, CLS, etc.)
3. Send analytics data to your Vercel project dashboard

You can verify the integration is working by:
1. Deploying the application to Vercel
2. Visiting pages on the deployed site
3. Checking the browser's Network tab for requests to Vercel Analytics endpoints
4. Viewing analytics data in your Vercel project dashboard under the Analytics section
